section: compiler
synopsis: Diagnostics can carry related source locations
issues: #22637
mrs: !16100

description: {
Diagnostics can now carry *related locations*: additional source spans beyond
the primary error span, such as the earlier binding sites in a
duplicate-definition error. Related locations are rendered as additional
carets (or, where the source cannot be displayed, listed under an ``At:``
heading), and are exposed to tooling via ``-fdiagnostics-as-json`` in the new
``relatedSpans`` field; the JSON schema version is bumped to 1.3.

"Duplicate" diagnostics (e.g. multiple declarations of the same name, or
duplicate exports) now report the *last* occurrence in source order as the
primary location, with the earlier occurrences as related locations,
matching the behaviour of other compilers.
}
